# 🔍 Step-by-step debugging (DO THIS EXACTLY)

## ✅ Step 1: Check failing operators

```bash
oc get co
```

Focus on:

* authentication
* ingress
* openshift-apiserver
* insights

---

## ✅ Step 2: Check pods with image pull issues

```bash
oc get pods -A | egrep -i "ImagePullBackOff|ErrImagePull|CrashLoopBackOff"
```

👉 If yes → THIS is your main problem

---

## ✅ Step 3: Restart all failed pods (safe)

```bash
oc get pods -A | egrep -i "ImagePullBackOff|ErrImagePull" | awk '{print $1, $2}' | while read ns pod; do
  oc delete pod $pod -n $ns
done
```

---

## ✅ Step 4: Check master node status

```bash
oc get nodes
```

If masters are:

* NotReady ❌
* SchedulingDisabled ❌

👉 Then MCP stuck because nodes unhealthy

---

## ✅ Step 5: Check MCP details (VERY IMPORTANT)

```bash
oc describe mcp master
```

Look for:

* Degraded reasons
* MachineConfig errors
* Kubelet failures

---

## ✅ Step 6: Check machine-config-daemon logs

Pick one master:

```bash
oc debug node/<master-node>
chroot /host
journalctl -u machine-config-daemon -f
```

